datavalue.value: President Leslie Gerald Rudolph Lynch Jerry Ford (King) Jr. (14 Jul 1913 - certain 26 Dec 2006)

value.text: Ford declined [the Green Bay Packers's] offer, and another offer from the Detroit Lions to play professional football, and instead made his way over into Yale to study law, then to the Navy to serve his country, then to the House of Representatives, and finally to the White House where, thankfully, the salary was a bit better.
There’s only one president who ... [...] ... received an offer to play professional football: Gerald Ford.
